# 1.Requirement

Name:101 E-Library 

Purpose: The purpose of our web application is to create an online library accessible to all users, providing free access to read books online. Additionally, users have the option to purchase physical copies if desired. The system allows users to access the latest book releases, search for books, experience online reading, make purchases, and reference previous user feedback on books they intend to read.
Users:

Readers: Individuals interested in accessing digital books, research papers, articles, etc.

Administrators: Manage the digital library, handle user accounts, upload and organize content, and oversee borrowing/returning processes.

## System Features (Classification)

## User-Side Features:

###  User Authentication and Profile Management:

User registration and login.

Profile creation and customization.

### Browse and Search:

Browse categories (fiction, non-fiction, genres, etc.).

Advanced search (by title, author, genre, keywords, etc.).

### Book Details:

View book summaries, author details, ratings, reviews, and availability status.

Preview chapters or excerpts.

### Reading Functions:

Read books online (in-browser reading).

Bookmark pages.

### Read online/Downloading:

Read online e-books for a specified period.

Download books for offline reading.

### User Interaction:

Rate books.

Write and view reviews/comments.

Share books or excerpts on social media.

## Admin-Side Features

### Content Management:

Upload, categorize, and manage digital books/documents.

Update book information (cover, description, etc.).

### User Management:

Manage user accounts (activate, deactivate, delete).

View transactions history and overdue books.

### Reports and Analytics:

Generate reports on book popularity, user activity, etc.

Monitor system usage statistics.
